x4freetext: Spectroscopically pure 99.99% vanadium foils of
12-mg/cm**2 thickness were interspersed with aluminium
foils of varying thicknesses acting as energy
degraders.
Irradiation periods were about 1 to 2 hours,
keeping in view the half-lives of the activities.

x4codes.shortRef: Jour: Applied Radiation and Isotopes, Vol.27, p.431 (1976)

x4freetext: The overall projected error in the present
experimentally  measured  cross sections was subdivided
into following categories:
High limit of the error due to non-uniformity
in the foil thickness.
The error in the flux determination.
The error in the detector efficiency.
Low limit of photopeak area uncertainty.
High limit of photopeak area uncertainty.

x4code.headerHelp: Digitizing error of incident particle energy

x4freetext: .Data-point reader uncertainty.
The error in the absolute abundances of the
charasteristic gamma-rays vary between 1-8%.
Other factors which may influence the cross section
measurements are the following:
the maximum error in the beam loss at the end of the
1.  Vanadium stack is calculated to be less than 2%
hense it is neglected.
2.  Straggling effects may introduce some error but are
neglected because for alpha particle the energy
straggling at the end of the stack is always much
smaller than the energy of the beam in the target foil
itself.
The above mentioned errors in the measurement of
experimental cross sections, do not include the
uncertainty of the nuclear data-half-lives of residual
nuclei, branching ratio etc that were taken from the
table of isotopes and nuclear data tables.
.By CAJAD.
